Stenodynerus
de Saussure, 1863

is a genus of small-sized potter wasps, comprising 168 species and 26 subspecies distributed in all global regions except for sub-Saharan Africa and 
Australia
.Of these, 45 species and 11 subspecies are recorded from the Palearctic region (Carpenter, unpublished). Most Palearctic species were revised by 

, but the subsequent description of several new species, taxonomic changes, and new records from the region make that revision outdated (

; 

; 

; 

, 

, 

, 

, 

, 

; 

; 

; 

). In his 1981 revision, Gusenleitner divided the Palearctic species into five informal species-groups, and characterized the 

fastidiosissimus

-group as follows: “ 
Mit Ausnahme je einer Färbungform und Subspecies haben die Arten Binden auf den Tergiten I-V (♀), bzw. I-VI (♂), die Augenausrandung ist nie gelb gezeichnet, das 2. Tergit ist vor dem Endrand im seitlichen Profil flach. Der Clypeus des Männchens ist gleichmässig flach konvex
” (= “With the exception of one color form and one subspecies each, the species have bands on tergites I-V (♀), or I-VI (♂), the eye margin is never marked yellow, the second tergite is flat in front of the apical edge in lateral view. Male clypeus is uniformly weakly convex”). It is to be noted that the black eye margin is not a constant character, as males always have a yellow line on the lower half of inner eye margin and, though rare, some females may present hints of a yellow line.

